#    How to Spot Potentially Harmful Browser Extensions:
#       Malicious extensions often try to hide their true intentions. Look out for these red flag
#       1.  Unexpected Installation
#       2.  Sudden Browser Behavior Changes
#       3.  Excessive Pop-up Ads
#       4.  Unexpected Redirects 
#       5.  Slowed Browser Performance
#       6.  Access to cookies, authentication tokens, or personal information
#       7.  Ability to read/write/modify web requests
#       8.  Ability to track keystrokes (like a keylogger)
#       9.  Access to your microphone or camera
#       10.  Vague or Generic Names
#       11.  Poor Reviews or Low Ratings
#       12.  Lack of Developer Information 
#       13.  Old or Unmaintained Extensions
#       14.  Sideloaded Extensions
_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

#    Steps how to Remove Potentially Harmful Browser Extensions:-
#      1. Open Your Browser's Extension Manager from the browser click on the three dots (menu) > More Tools > Extensions, or type chrome://extensions/ in the address bar.
#      2. Go to Chrome extension and then view extension.
#      3. Identify and Remove Suspicious Extensions.
#      4. Restart Your Browser to ensure that the changes apply on that.
#      5. Check Browser Notifications and Permissions.
#      6. Clear Browser Cache and Cookies to enhance security.
#      7. Scan Your System for Malware and install the antivirus.
#      8. Update Your Browser and install additional security tools.

